{"word":"H3048 - יְדַעְיָה - Yᵉdaʻyâh - yed-ah-yaw' - Jedaiah","slug":"H3048","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">יְדַעְיָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Yᵉdaʻyâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>yed-ah-yaw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Jedaiah"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>ידעיה</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>yeda‛yâh</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>yed-ah-yaw'</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Jedaiah = \"Jehovah has known\" <ol><li>a priest in Jerusalem</li><li>a man who returned with Zerubbabel</li><li>a ruler of the priests in the days of Jeshua</li><li>a post exilic priest</li><li>one honoured by Jehovah, perhaps one of the above</li></ol> <p />Origin: from <a href=\"#/H3045\">H3045</a> and <a href=\"#/H3050\">H3050</a> <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Masculine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1843\">H1843</a>, <a href=\"#/H1844\">H1844</a>, <a href=\"#/H1845\">H1845</a>, <a href=\"#/H1847\">H1847</a>, <a href=\"#/H3037\">H3037</a>, <a href=\"#/H3043\">H3043</a>, <a href=\"#/H3045\">H3045</a>, <a href=\"#/H3047\">H3047</a>, <a href=\"#/H3049\">H3049</a>, <a href=\"#/H4069\">H4069</a>, <a href=\"#/H4093\">H4093</a>, <a href=\"#/H4129\">H4129</a>, <a href=\"#/H4130\">H4130</a>"}]}